> This Sweet Potato Cottage Pie is bursting full of flavours and makes the perfect
> dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!

Put a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes.

Peel and grate the @?garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Chop the @sweet potato{1} and @white potatoes{450%g} into roughly 2cm chunks (peel
first if you prefer).

Heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef and pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use
a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Add the garlic and @sliced mushrooms{80%g} to the pan, then cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the chopped potatoes to your pan of boiling water and simmer until
you can easily slip a #knife{} through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a
knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @milk{1%splash} and mash until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the @Worcester sauce{7.5%ml} to the pan and
bubble away until evaporated, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @tomato passata{1%jar}, @beef stock paste{10%g}
and @water{50%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Preheat your #grill{} to medium-high.

Transfer the mince filling to an #ovenproof dish{} and top with an even layer of
mash.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g} over the top, then grill until golden and
bubbling, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once your cottage pie is ready, allow to stand for ~{2%minutes} before serving
on plates. Enjoy!